cdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uaegonsoundforge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aegon Soundforge</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/10/02 1:40:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2338.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Marauder's mire?</span><hr size=1> I agree totally.  I transfered over for a month to check it out even though I figured it wasn't going to be all they said.  All you get for your money is a fast response time to petitions and, frankly, I'd just as soon wait awhile for that price.  I saw a total of 3 actual GM events happen (not those silly Arena events they have every day but actual storyed events).  They were all way overcrowded. The last one I went to took place partly in PoH and a bunch of us didn't even get to go because the GMs were afraid they'd crash the zone if any more people ported up.  <br>
<br>
About half the people I met there were transfering back to their original servers when I did.VI might break even on Legends but they aren't going to do much beyond that until they seriously rethink how they do things there.  They could start by adding some SH only zones that have some originality and start holding events for ALL levels that actually effect the world in some way.  That's probably asking too much though. <p>Aegon, 56 Troubadour </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/urick7475.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rick7475</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/10/02 7:03:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2338.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ditto for me</span><hr size=1> Spent a month there as a 48 level. Really sucked for that level, except for the price of items for mid range.<br>
<br>
I attended a GM event in LOIO where Cazic-Thule appeared and began gathering his minions to invade FV. The evil followers went to the CZ side, where as the good followers went to the Tunare side, who appeared in FV.<br>
<br>
You had to de-guild to become a member of Tunare's guild, and fight (pvp) against the people who joined CZ.<br>
<br>
We had a big fight outside the fort in LOIO, and since many of the players on Stormhammer were mega uber 60's needless to say it was not a pleasant experience to fight all red conned players at level 48. <br>
<br>
CZ went down, someone ninja-looted him, and that was that. Never learned what he dropped.<br>
<br>
It was kind of fun, but I think you had more fun if you were 55+. In fact, I have no idea why anyone under 52 would want to go there, since most of the people are high level, and a lot of guilds don't take you unless your over 52. Sure, there were some guilds who took people over 45, or under 40, but very few.<br>
<br>
Some of the zones were practically empty for pick up groups. I brought my level 15 warrior to High Pass to fight orcs. Nada, no one there most of the time.<br>
<br>
Other GM events were just plain silly. Runt-ball and last man standing competitions that got old after the first 2 weeks.<br>
<br>
I have a feeling a lot of uber 60's came there to loot less camped areas, then leave.<br>
<br>
Certainly not worth the price, IMHO. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter>Vazaelle.com Community Center</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1>General Discussion</a> <font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href="http://www.vazaelle.com">Vazaelle.com</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.8<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  